songs.title: Disengage
songs.lyrics:
I should have told you
with all that we been through
how much I feel
I don't wanna know it's real
I don't wanna lose you
I don't wanna lose you
go ahead and look inside
you don't have to hide
promise me you'll stay
by my side
everything that haunts me
all the things that taunt me
can't fall asleep I know you don't want me

we're building up just to fall out
it's entropy we're breaking down
you're missing the point so i'm blacking out
and I hate to talk so I just write it down
don't fuck with me now
life is no fun until I take the crown
I'm just myself can't be someone else
don't use a pseudonym
It's just the hand that i'm dealt
wanna know how I feel get a lock pick
armored up growing toxic
drowning in percs till I panic
I'll fade to a ghost watch me vanish
